        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 4:12PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Kellerton Church, or 7 miles south of Goose Lake, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayti, Hazel, Thomas, Kellerton Church, and Hamlin Education Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
northeastern South Dakota.</instruction>
